context.en:
**NorthStar Retail** runs a Customer Support Resolution Agent (Claude Opus 4.8, Agent SDK) across web chat, email, and SMS. Until now it only answered policy questions. The new release adds **live account context**: it must read CRM customer records and the order-management system, issue refunds, and, when it cannot resolve an issue, **hand off to a human support agent** with a clean summary.

The team exposes the back-office systems through MCP. The CRM and orders run as a **remote Streamable HTTP server**; a legacy ledger runs as a **local stdio server** on the support host. A pre-launch security review flagged the proposed connector config below.

```jsonc
// mcp_servers passed on the Messages API (MCP connector)
[
  {
    "type": "url",
    "name": "crm_orders",
    "url": "https://mcp.northstar.internal/crm",
    // ONE broad OAuth token reused for CRM, orders, AND the payments/refund tool
    "authorization_token": "Bearer ${OMNI_TOKEN}",
    "tool_configuration": { "enabled": true }
    // no per-tool allow/denylist; issue_refund is callable directly
  }
]
```

**Security review findings:** (1) one over-broad token spans read-only lookups *and* state-changing payments; (2) `issue_refund` can fire with no human checkpoint; (3) the CI smoke test runs `claude -p` headlessly and the CRM server's tools never load. Latency budget is 4 s P50; the system prompt + tool defs + last-30-days policy manual are stable across turns; transcripts are long.

context.fr:
**NorthStar Retail** exploite un agent de résolution du support client (Claude Opus 4.8, Agent SDK) sur le chat web, l'e-mail et le SMS. Jusqu'ici il ne répondait qu'aux questions de politique. La nouvelle version ajoute le **contexte de compte en direct** : il doit lire les fiches client du CRM et le système de gestion des commandes, émettre des remboursements et, lorsqu'il ne peut pas résoudre un problème, **transférer à un agent humain** avec un résumé propre.

L'équipe expose les systèmes de back-office via MCP. Le CRM et les commandes tournent comme un **serveur distant Streamable HTTP** ; un grand livre hérité tourne comme un **serveur local stdio** sur l'hôte de support. Une revue de sécurité avant lancement a signalé la configuration de connecteur ci-dessous.

```jsonc
// mcp_servers transmis sur l'API Messages (connecteur MCP)
[
  {
    "type": "url",
    "name": "crm_orders",
    "url": "https://mcp.northstar.internal/crm",
    // UN jeton OAuth large réutilisé pour CRM, commandes ET l'outil paiements/remboursement
    "authorization_token": "Bearer ${OMNI_TOKEN}",
    "tool_configuration": { "enabled": true }
    // aucun allow/denylist par outil ; issue_refund est appelable directement
  }
]
```

**Conclusions de la revue de sécurité :** (1) un jeton trop large couvre les recherches en lecture seule *et* les paiements modifiant l'état ; (2) `issue_refund` peut se déclencher sans point de contrôle humain ; (3) le test de fumée CI lance `claude -p` sans interaction et les outils du serveur CRM ne se chargent jamais. Budget de latence : 4 s P50 ; le prompt système + les définitions d'outils + le manuel de politique des 30 derniers jours sont stables d'un tour à l'autre ; les transcriptions sont longues.

context.en:
**SpecForge** is an internal API-backed service at a fintech. Given a natural-language feature request, it must emit a strongly-typed artifact: a TypeScript module plus its OpenAPI fragment. Reliability matters more than latency, downstream codegen consumes the JSON directly, so a single malformed field breaks the build.

The team runs the generation behind Claude Opus 4.8 through a small pipeline: a **router** classifies the request into one of four artifact families, then the generator produces the artifact, and a separate **evaluator** scores it. The generated artifact is returned via a tool whose `input_schema` is reproduced below. Every request shares a large, byte-identical preamble (coding standards + 6k tokens of repo conventions); only the trailing feature request varies. A nightly **eval harness** replays 2,000 frozen requests in CI and grades the output; the project's Claude Code config also exposes a `/specforge` slash command and a GitHub Action that runs the same harness on every PR.

```json
{
  "name": "emit_artifact",
  "description": "Return the generated typed code artifact and its API spec.",
  "strict": true,
  "input_schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {
      "language":   { "type": "string", "enum": ["typescript"] },
      "module":     { "type": "string" },
      "openapi":    { "type": "object" },
      "http_status":{ "type": "integer" },
      "notes":      { "type": "string" }
    },
    "required": ["language", "module", "openapi", "http_status"]
  }
}
```

The team is now tightening correctness, cost, and the eval loop before GA.

context.fr:
